    "summary": "The transcript follows a high school teacher asking for an explanation of substantive due process, eventually leading to a discussion on the tension between \"living constitutionalism\" and \"originalism.\" The assistant consistently advocates for the living document theory, dismisses originalist critiques as flawed, and frames the doctrine as an essential protection against government overreach.",
